f:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. SDL Trados is best suited for professional translators, enterprises, LSPs, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Unbabel, meanwhile, shines for customer support teams, global companies, service desks, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 1984, SDL Trados describes itself as \"Industry-standard CAT tool for professional translation and localization.\" Unbabel, established in 2013, positions itself as \"AI-powered translation combining machine translation with human editors.\" With 29 years between them, SDL Trados brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Unbabel offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
10:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **SDL Trados** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (9 vs 7). However, this does not mean Unbabel is a poor choice — far from it. Unbabel excels in its own right, particularly for customer support teams and global companies.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value industry standard with largest market share, go with SDL Trados. If human-quality translation at scale matters more to you, Unbabel is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
